toiler
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a hard, persistent or conscientious worker; grafter (often qualified by great, hard, real)
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1935 Havelock e.g.: He drinks, never pays his bills, but I'll say this for him, he's a great toiler
